The paper also mentions the need for real-time action in automated decision-making systems, which suggests a focus on practical applications. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Signal Processing), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
